    "title": "Midsummer, was it, when They died --",
    "author": "Emily Dickinson",
    "type": "poetry",
    "subtitle": "A Classic Poem",
    "bgImage": "url(./images/bg-dickinson.jpg)",
    "content": "<p>Midsummer, was it, when They died --<br>\nA full, and perfect time --<br>\nThe Summer closed upon itself<br>\nIn Consummated Bloom --\n</p>\n<p>The Corn, her furthest kernel filled<br>\nBefore the coming Flail --<br>\nWhen These -- leaned unto Perfectness --<br>\nThrough Haze of Burial --\n</p>\n<br>\n<p><em>Tags: poetry, classic, dickinson, american</em></p>"
